Overview
========

szl is a tiny, embeddable scripting engine inspired by Tcl and shell. It
combines the simplicity of shell scripting with the power of Tcl and a rich
standard library that includes bindings for popular libraries.
  __________________________________________________
 /                                                  \
 | szl 0.1 6f1e278e58cc9742c31bef959ab3afe9b8aa7c65 |
 | >>> load zlib                                    |
 | >>> zlib.crc32 "Hello, world!"                   |
 | 3957769958                                       |
 | >>>                                              |
 \__________________________________________________/

For more information, see the user manual at http://www.dimakrasner.com/szl.

Building
========

  $ make
  $ make install

Documentation
=============

To build the user manual:

  $ cd doc; make szl.html

To build the API documentation:

  $ cd doc; make api_docs

